Which competitive comparison of the WebSphere Application Server family and Oracle
WebLogic Server is correct?
A. Oracle WebLogic Server provides a smaller range of functionality, features and
operating system support compared to the WAS family. WebLogic is higher cost on
average when comparing equivalent capabilities to WAS.
B. Oracle WebLogic Server provides the same range of functionality, features and
operating system support as the WAS family. WebLogic is higher cost on average when
comparing equivalent capabilities to WAS.
C. Oracle WebLogic Server provides the same range of functionality, features and
operating system support as the WAS family. WebLogic is lower cost on average when
comparing equivalent capabilities to WAS.
D. Oracle WebLogic Server provides a smaller range of functionality, features and
operating system support as the WAS family. WebLogic is lower cost on average when
comparing equivalent capabilities to WAS.
Answer: A

A. Red Hat JBoss
B. Oracle WebLogic
C. Apache Tomcat
D. Oracle Glassfish
E. All the above
F. None of the above
Answer: F

Prolifics Inc. published a whitepaper in 2012 with a total cost of ownership (TCO) study
comparing WAS ND v8.5 and JBoss Enterprise Application Platform v6 over a five year
period. These products are proposed when customer requirements call for elevated
qualities of service and application availability. The study showed that WAS ND provides
significant cost savings compared to JBoss EAP except in the area of:
A. Hardware
B. Application management
C. Infrastructure management
D. Software licensing
E. Risk and downtime
Answer: B
